  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Let <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant="fraktur">m</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> be a local Noetherian ring, let M be a finitely generated R -module and let <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>•</mo></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mo>∂</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>•</mo></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> be a free resolution of M . We find a uniform bound h such that the Artin–Rees containment <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mi>F</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub><mo>∩</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">Im</mi><mspace width="0.2em"></mspace><msub><mrow><mo>∂</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>⊆</mo><msup><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>−</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">Im</mi><mspace width="0.2em"></mspace><msub><mrow><mo>∂</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> holds for all integers <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>i</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>d</mi></math> , for all integers <math altimg="si370.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>n</mi><mo>≥</mo><mi>h</mi></math> , and for all ideals I of R . In fact, we show that a considerably stronger statement holds. The uniform bound h holds for all ideals and all resolutions of d th syzygy modules. In order to prove our statements, we introduce the concept of Koszul annihilating sequences.</subfield>
